    "description": "Dr. Reddy's Laboratories has an exciting opening for a Senior Doctor at our Bhubaneswar office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Dr. Reddy's Laboratories:\nDr. Reddy's Laboratories is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Flexible working hours\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Dr. Reddy's Laboratories!",
